content.description: Start holds are low and left of the Horn of Africa shaped flake, walk around and clean the top out if possible. Immediately to the right of "Hey, pro tip"Â
content.protection: one crash pad would be sufficient.
content.location: On right face of Christine Rock, immediately next to Hey, pro tip. Lies in a stripe of non lichen and moss covered rock, look for the horn of Africa shaped flake.

content.description: Fairly obvious holds littered everywhere, might have to clear some moss otherwise holds are solid. little choss flakes here and there. The further left you climb the easier it gets.
content.location: When facing the rock, there is a triangle shaped feature that bisects the left and right side of the face, Hey, pro tip is immediately to the right of this feature.

content.description: South Facing boulder, spotted with lichens and moss. The routes have been reasonably clear of choss, however it is around...Probably only need one crash pad.
